To start a job inside the pod(deployment) you need:
1) Write a .yaml file like this:
 *scala.yaml
apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: scala-deployment
spec:
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: scala
  replicas: 1
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: scala
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: scala
        image: lulkaval/scala:latest
        ports:
        - containerPort: 80
          protocol: TCP
        command: ["/bin/sh", "-ec", "sleep 1000"]  
                  
2) Start your k8s, e.g.
minikube start

3) Write to create a deployment
kubectl apply -f ./scala.yaml 

4) Write to find this pod name
kubectl get pods 
Be sure, that your pod is running (it becomes unactive after "sleep 1000" ends)

5) kubectl exec <POD_NAME> -- java -cp "./*" load.LoadStarter ...(params)
